Vintage illustration of an ancient tree with roots made of angular, interconnected brackets and tags, its trunk formed from layered parchment scrolls containing intricate geometric patterns. The branches split and transform as they rise - one side bearing leaves shaped like structured data nodes in deep burgundy and gold, the other side blooming with organic flowing shapes in warm amber and cream. A stream of translucent ribbons flows between the branches, suggesting transformation and metamorphosis. The background features aged sepia tones with subtle crosshatching, reminiscent of Victorian-era botanical illustrations. Small birds made of simple geometric shapes perch throughout, watching the transformation unfold. The overall composition suggests evolution, ancestry, and the elegant conversion of one form into another.
